text.tspan: Let Us Rise Up and Build
All the walls are crushed and broken,
And the gates once burned with fire,
But we will not be discouraged,
We will fight and build our part.
To God this is our memorial;
Now the walls are high and mighty;
All our foes, they shake in fear.
The people return and they gather
We may mourn and weep in sorrow,
But our God wants us to feast.
Come in, eat the fat, drink the sweet wine!
